"""Exercise 2 (and Solution)

The exercise comes first (with a few extras if you want the extra challenge or want to spend more time), followed by a discussion. Enjoy!

Ask the user for a number. Depending on whether the number is even or odd, print out an appropriate message to the user. 
Hint: how does an even / odd number react differently when divided by 2?

Extras:

If the number is a multiple of 4, print out a different message.
Ask the user for two numbers: one number to check (call it num) and one number to divide by (check). 
If check divides evenly into num, tell that to the user. If not, print a different appropriate message.
"""
while(True):
    num1 = int(input("Enter a number: "))
    check = int(input("Enter an integer to check the divisibility: "))
    if (num1%check == 0):
        print(str(num1)+" is completely divisible to "+str(check))
    else:
        print(str(num1)+" is not divisible to "+str(check))
        break
